The paper deals with natural language text and proposes a method for optimizing hashcode representations for biomedical relation extraction tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The proposed method involves nearly unsupervised learning, which involves optimizing hash functions without using class labels. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval and classification tasks, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) as it involves the use of hashcode representations for text analysis.
